        body: '<p><strong>Backout plan:</strong> Every change must have a documented rollback procedure. Changes should be reversible wherever possible. Always maintain verified, current backups before beginning — some changes are very difficult to reverse without them. Test the backout procedure in the sandbox before deployment.</p><p><strong>Maintenance window:</strong> Changes are scheduled during low-activity periods — typically nights or weekends — to minimize user impact. Some environments (24/7 operations, holiday retail) require careful timing around business cycles. Affected users must receive advance notification via email and calendar updates.</p><p><strong>Standard Operating Procedure (SOP):</strong> Change management processes must be documented, published (e.g., on the intranet), and maintained as living documents that are updated whenever processes change.</p>',
