        body: 'Hashing produces a fixed-length fingerprint of any data — even a single character change produces a completely different fingerprint. Digital signatures combine hashing with asymmetric cryptography to prove both that data is unchanged AND that a specific key holder signed it. These tools are foundational to Security+ and appear in many exam topics.',
