          '<strong>Root CA:</strong> Self-signed; pre-trusted by browsers/OS; private key kept offline.',
          '<strong>Intermediate CA:</strong> Signed by root; signs end-entity certs — isolates root from daily operations.',
          '<strong>Wildcard cert:</strong> *.example.com — covers all immediate subdomains; uses SAN extension.',
          '<strong>Self-signed cert:</strong> Not browser-trusted — requires manual trust installation on all clients.',
          '<strong>CRL:</strong> CA-maintained list of revoked certs — large, slow to update.',
