          'Trust chain: Root CA (offline, pre-trusted) → Intermediate CA → End-entity certificate.',
          'CSR: applicant generates key pair, sends public key to CA, CA validates and returns signed certificate.',
          'Revocation: CRL (large, slow list); OCSP (real-time query); OCSP Stapling (server pre-fetches and delivers status in handshake).',
          'Wildcard certs (*.example.com) cover all immediate subdomains; self-signed certs require manual trust installation.',
