        body: '<p><strong>Data at rest</strong> — Data stored on a storage device (HDD, SSD, flash drive, tape). Protected by:</p><ul><li><strong>Full disk encryption (FDE)</strong> — Encrypts the entire drive; BitLocker (Windows), FileVault (macOS), LUKS (Linux). Protects lost/stolen devices.</li><li><strong>Database encryption</strong> — Transparent Data Encryption (TDE) encrypts database files at rest.</li><li><strong>File/folder encryption</strong> — Windows EFS encrypts individual files.</li><li><strong>Access control lists</strong> — Limit who can read or modify stored files; only authorized users can access data.</li></ul><p><strong>Data in transit</strong> — Data moving across a network. Not much natural protection as it travels through switches, routers, and untrusted networks. Protected by:</p><ul><li><strong>TLS (Transport Layer Security)</strong> — Encrypts application-layer communication (HTTPS, SMTPS, IMAPS).</li><li><strong>IPsec</strong> — Encrypts network-layer communication between hosts or networks.</li><li><strong>VPN</strong> — Encrypts all traffic between endpoints across untrusted networks.</li></ul>',
