        body: 'Access control is the process of ensuring only authorized rights are exercised. Policy definition determines what rights exist; policy enforcement ensures they are applied. The five primary access control models — MAC, DAC, RBAC, rule-based, and ABAC — represent different ways of making authorization decisions, from rigid labels to complex context-aware rules.',
