        body: 'Digital forensics collects and protects information relating to an intrusion. RFC 3227 provides best practices for evidence collection and archiving. The standard process is acquisition, analysis, and reporting. All steps must be detail-oriented with extensive notes, because what happens now determines whether evidence is admissible in future legal proceedings.',
